a parking fee is required to park on any california state university campus according to state law.disabled parking spaces are located in all university parking facilities. disabled parking placards and license plates are not honored in campus red zones, yellow zones, white zones, or green zones.persons with temporary disabilities that may preclude or impair walking for distances should contact the accessible education center (aec)at 408-924-6000 for assistance and additional information. employees may also contact the employment accommodations resource center (earc)at 408-924-6003.